    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-20T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="146"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/923: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-20T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. For <persName corresp="#p_AG1">Auchincloss</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_PFL1">Polk</persName>. Your 118, November 18.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d146fn14">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_197">p. 197</ref>.</note>
                    Department would like you to go ahead on the plan outlined in your 99 with the
                    modifications made by our Number 36.<note n="15" xml:id="d146fn15">No. 99 is
                        printed on <ref target="#pg_194">p. 194</ref>; No. 36, on <ref
                            target="#pg_196">p. 196</ref>.</note> Suggested that
                        <persName>Strauss</persName>
                    <note n="16" xml:id="d146fn16">
                        <persName>Albert Strauss</persName>, Vice Governor of the Federal Reserve
                        Board.</note> or <persName>Kent</persName>
                    <note n="17" xml:id="d146fn17">
                        <persName>William Kent</persName>, member of the United States Tariff
                        Commission.</note> be taken over as financial adviser … President said he
                    would telegraph for some one when he was needed. This seems to be the plan they
                    are following in regard to representatives of the various boards. President and
                    commissioners plan to sail about December 3d. Commission has not yet been
                    determined. Strictly confidentially, President taking with him <persName>Cary
                        Grayson</persName>
                    <note n="18" xml:id="d146fn18">Rear <persName>Admiral Cary T.
                        Grayson</persName>, physician to the President.</note> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CG1">Creel</persName>, not <persName>Tumulty</persName>.<note
                        n="19" xml:id="d146fn19">
                        <persName>Joseph P. Tumulty</persName>, secretary to the President.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
